## Authority

- **Normative** definitions and allowed positions for contract syntax live in **`sv0doc/`** (grammar + typing/contract sections).
- The [vision and design](http://development.sasankvishnubhatla.net/tcowmbh/task/sv0-compiler-vision-and-design.html) explains *why* contracts exist; it does not override **`sv0doc/`** for what the bootstrap compiler accepts today.

## Clause families (conceptual)

- **`requires` / `ensures` / `loop_invariant`** — boolean conditions; some forms lower to runtime checks in the SML bootstrap (see **`sv0c/doc/compiler-passes.md`**).
- **`forall` / `exists`** — quantified contract expressions; valid only in contract positions per spec. VM support may lag C for some shapes; check **`sv0doc/`** and vm-parity policy before assuming parity.
- **`no_alias` / `borrows` / `old` / `result`** — memory and call contracts; lowering is backend-sensitive (**C** vs **VM**). Do not generalize from one backend to the other without tests and spec alignment.

## Agent rules

- When adding or changing contract **syntax**, **checking**, or **lowering**, update **`sv0doc/`** first if behavior is meant to be normative, then tasks, then **`sv0c/`**, then validation (unit, integration, vm-parity where applicable).
- Do not introduce new contract keywords or clause meanings from the vision doc alone.
- Prefer **behavioral** diagnostic parity when tightening messages; see **`task/sv0-toolchain-milestone-3-self-host.Rmd`** (stakeholder decisions).

